# CODEOWNERS — automated reviewer routing.
#
# GitHub uses this file to auto-request reviews when a PR touches a
# matching path. The first matching rule wins, so list specific paths
# BEFORE generic ones. Treat the @teams here as the source of truth
# for "who must approve a PR touching X."
#
# Sync any team-rename here in the same PR as the GitHub change — a
# missing team becomes a silent "no reviewer required."

# ── Default: the platform team gets pinged on anything not otherwise routed.
*                                                       @platform

# ── Security-critical surfaces — two approvals required (configured at the
# repo-level branch protection rule; CODEOWNERS just routes the requests).
/supabase/migrations/                                   @platform @data-eng
/supabase/migrations/*RLS*                              @platform @data-eng @security
/supabase/migrations/*POLICY*                           @platform @data-eng @security
/supabase/migrations/*tenants*                          @platform @data-eng @security
/supabase/functions/                                    @platform
/supabase/functions/_shared/                            @platform

# ── Auth / RLS code paths
